### Specific Values Explained

| Variable | Dark value | Light value | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|-------------|-----------|
| `--bg` | `#0f1117` | `#fafbfc` | Off-white, softer than pure white |
| `--card` | `rgba(255,255,255,0.04)` | `rgba(0,0,0,0.02)` | Inverted: slight darkening instead of lightening |
| `--panel` | `#0f131d` | `#ffffff` | Pure white panels on off-white background |
| `--text` | `#e9ecf5` | `#1a1d26` | Near-black for readability |
| `--muted` | `#9aa3b5` | `#5a6478` | Mid-gray, WCAG AA compliant on white |
| `--accent` | `#7ce7c1` | `#0ea573` | Darker green for contrast on white background |
| `--accent-2` | `#8ab8ff` | `#3b7ddd` | Darker blue for contrast |
| `--border` | `rgba(255,255,255,0.08)` | `rgba(0,0,0,0.08)` | Same opacity, inverted base |
| `--shadow` | `0 20px 60px rgba(0,0,0,0.35)` | `0 20px 60px rgba(0,0,0,0.06)` | Much softer shadows on light |

The hardcoded `.site-header` background (`rgba(15, 17, 23, 0.85)`) on line 52 of `styles.css` is the most critical override -- it would appear as a dark bar on an otherwise white page.

