## Part 1: Flipbook Landing Animation

### Strategy

Create an inline `<script>` at the bottom of `DHGSVR25/index.html` plus a `<div id="flipbook-overlay">` immediately after `<body>`. No external JS files needed since this is a single-page feature.

### Detailed Implementation

**1.1 HTML Structure** -- Add to `DHGSVR25/index.html` right after `<body>`:

```html
<div id="flipbook-overlay" aria-hidden="true">
  <div id="flipbook-canvas"></div>
</div>
```

The overlay sits above everything (z-index: 9999), covers the full viewport, has a white background (matching the new theme).

**1.2 CSS for the overlay** -- Add as a `<style>` block in the `<head>` of `DHGSVR25/index.html`:

```css
#flipbook-overlay {
  position: fixed;
  inset: 0;
  z-index: 9999;
  background: #ffffff;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  transition: opacity 0.8s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
}

#flipbook-overlay.fade-out {
  opacity: 0;
  pointer-events: none;
}

#flipbook-canvas {
  width: min(90vw, 800px);
  aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
  border-radius: 12px;
  overflow: hidden;
  box-shadow: 0 20px 60px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
}

#flipbook-canvas img {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  display: block;
}

body.flipbook-active {
  overflow: hidden;
}
```

**1.3 JavaScript Approach** -- Add as `<script>` before `</body>`:

```javascript
(function() {
  const images = [
    'screenshots/glacial-mint-newyear.png',
    'screenshots/floriahimmel-newyear.png',
    'screenshots/tofumisoshiru-newyear.png',
    // ... all 23 filenames in a visually pleasing order
    // (mix newyear and portfolio screenshots for variety)
  ];

  const overlay = document.getElementById('flipbook-overlay');
  const canvas  = document.getElementById('flipbook-canvas');

  // Phase 1: Preload all images
  document.body.classList.add('flipbook-active');
  const loaded = [];
  let loadCount = 0;

  images.forEach((src, i) => {
    const img = new Image();
    img.src = src;
    loaded[i] = img;
    img.onload = img.onerror = () => {
      loadCount++;
      if (loadCount === images.length) startFlipbook();
    };
  });

  // Fallback: start after 3s even if not all loaded
  setTimeout(() => { if (loadCount < images.length) startFlipbook(); }, 3000);

  function startFlipbook() {
    let frame = 0;
    let interval = 120; // ms per frame, starts moderate
    const totalCycles = 2; // cycle through all images N times
    const totalFrames = images.length * totalCycles;
    let elapsed = 0;

    // Insert first image
    canvas.appendChild(loaded[0]);

    function tick() {
      frame++;
      if (frame >= totalFrames) {
        endFlipbook();
        return;
      }

      const imgIndex = frame % images.length;
      canvas.innerHTML = '';
      canvas.appendChild(loaded[imgIndex]);

      // Easing: start fast (80ms), slow down toward end (200ms)
      const progress = frame / totalFrames;
      const currentInterval = 80 + (progress * progress) * 200;

      setTimeout(tick, currentInterval);
    }

    setTimeout(tick, interval);
  }

  function endFlipbook() {
    // Hold last image briefly
    setTimeout(() => {
      overlay.classList.add('fade-out');
      document.body.classList.remove('flipbook-active');
      // Remove overlay from DOM after transition
      overlay.addEventListener('transitionend', () => {
        overlay.remove();
      });
    }, 400);
  }
})();
```

### Key Design Decisions

- **Timing curve**: The flipbook starts at ~80ms/frame (12.5 fps -- energetic), then decelerates quadratically to ~280ms/frame as it ends, creating a "settling" feel like a physical flipbook.
- **2 full cycles**: With 23 images and 2 cycles = 46 frames. At average ~150ms per frame, total animation is roughly 7 seconds. This is long enough to be memorable but short enough not to frustrate.
- **Preload strategy**: All 23 images are loaded via `new Image()` before the animation starts. Total payload is 3.1MB, which on a reasonable connection loads in 1-3 seconds. A 3-second fallback timeout ensures the animation starts even on slow connections.
- **Graceful degradation**: If JavaScript is disabled, the overlay `div` will be visible but the page behind it still exists. Could add `<noscript><style>#flipbook-overlay{display:none}</style></noscript>` as a fallback.
- **No `requestAnimationFrame`**: Using `setTimeout` with variable delays is intentional -- the "pata-pata" feel comes from discrete frame jumps, not smooth animation. rAF would lock to 60fps and lose the flipbook character.

### Image Ordering

The array should be curated for visual variety. Suggested order: alternate between newyear cards (colorful, festive) and portfolio pages (varied designs). This creates visual rhythm. The specific order:

```
marinakawaguchi-newyear, c426, glacial-mint-newyear, floriahimmel,
tofumisoshiru-newyear, siraha0611, finnapop-newyear, anine998,
uwuhhhj-newyear, sonobemasashi-web, lovpipit-newyear, final-ke,
